~ shop
Shopkeeper: Come in. I know who you are and why you're here. No need to get into it right now. You're probably exhausted. We've got time. 
Shopkeeper: That there's your room. I've readied a change of clothes and a warm bath for you. 
Shopkeeper: Get some sleep. Tomorrow we wake early. Lots of work to be done, and I'm guessing a lot of talking, too. 
Shopkeeper: I'm sure you've got loads of questions for me. Don't worry, I'll answer each and every one of them, as best I can. 
Shopkeeper: But not now. My daughter, Sarah, is fast asleep. She's been helping me out all day and I'd hate for us to wake her up with our chatter. 
Shopkeeper: I'll see you in the morning. Good night. 
- Alright then. 
	Sarah: [wait=1.5]...Dad? What's going on? Who is that?
	Shopkeeper: Go back to bed, sweetie. Everything's fine. 
	Sarah: I had that bad dream again. They came back. 
	Shopkeeper: Go back to bed. I'm right behind you. 
	Shopkeeper: [wait=1.5]Have to go. See you tomorrow. 
	- Sorry I woke her up.
		Shopkeeper: No harm done. It wasn't you. 
		Shopkeeper: Good night. => END 
	- All good?
		Shopkeeper: Yeah, don't worry about it. Good night. => END
	- Night. => END
